      "messageBody": "…, 15 modules\n\nThis commit transforms Dealix from a managed services platform into a\nself-serve SaaS Operating System for Saudi companies.\n\nPhase 1 — SaaS Foundation:\n- Subscription billing engine with 5 plans (Free/Starter/Growth/Scale/Enterprise)\n- Proration on upgrades/downgrades, recurring invoices, Moyasar integration\n- Self-serve onboarding: signup → tenant → plan → payment → wizard\n- Feature gating middleware + per-tenant feature flags\n- Customer dashboard with KPIs, notifications, quick actions\n- Tenant billing settings with invoice history\n\nPhase 2 — Core Business OS:\n- CRM enhancements: activities, meetings, notes\n- Projects & Tasks with time tracking and milestones\n- Support Desk: tickets, comments, SLA tracking, knowledge base\n- Document Management: folders, documents, permissions\n\nPhase 3 — ERP Suite:\n- HR: employees, attendance, leave (annual/sick/hajj/maternity), payroll with GOSI\n- Inventory: warehouses, SKUs, stock movements, suppliers, purchase orders\n- Finance GL: Chart of Accounts, journal entries (double-entry), trial balance, bank reconciliation\n\nPhase 4 — AI & Intelligence:\n- AI Co-Pilot: daily brief, pipeline analysis, financial health, inventory forecast\n\nFrontend (Next.js + Tailwind):\n- /signup, /onboarding, /[tenant]/dashboard, /[tenant]/settings/billing\n- /[tenant]/projects, /[tenant]/hr, /[tenant]/inventory\n\nDatabase: 72 tables total, including 29 new ERP tables\nAPI: 993 routes total\n\nAll Saudi-compliant: ZATCA e-invoicing, PDPL-native, approval-first architecture.",
      "messageHeadline": "feat: Complete SaaS ERP transformation — 72 DB tables, 993 API routes…",
